Lanalyse ICA (Integrated Context Analysis) montre les aires de convergence de hauts niveaux de rcurrence de linscurit alimentaire et la propensit majeure aux chocs naturels (inondations, scheresses, glissements de terrain). Lanalyse de risques de chocs naturels en est dcoule. Ces analyses de 2017 furent un effort conjoint entre le Bureau rgional du programme dalimentation mondiale Dakar (RBD), de leur Unit en analyse gospatiale (GIS) du bureau-mre et de leur division Programme.

Les facteurs varient par rgion comme on peut le voir ci-bas.

Survol gographique de facteurs cl

The North-Eastern regions of Burkina Faso (eg. Sahel, Centre-Nord) are more vulnerable, with high flood and drought risk. These regions also have a population more vulnerable to food insecurity and larger number of IDPs relative to the rest of the country. The countrys humanitarian presence is also most focused on these regions.

Tabular overview of key factors

Populations facing high hazard risk

We see a greater total population in regions facing high flooding risk. By this factor alone, we could perhaps estimate that flooding would have a larger humanitarian impact.

This figure shows that a significant majority of humanitarian activities are within the WASH cluster, with a notable number also for Nutrition and Health.
